President Joe Biden has announced his intention to nominate Irving W. Bailey II to serve as a Member on the Development Finance Corporation Board of Directors. Bailey has been a Member of the Board of Directors of the United States International Development Finance Corporation since 2019. Prior to that, he had a 35-year career in the financial services industry and served as Chairman and CEO of Providian Corporation. Bailey has also held positions as Vice Chairman of Aegon and Chairman of its Risk Committee. He has served as a director for various public and private companies, including Hospira, Inc. and Computer Sciences Corporation. Bailey recently retired as Trustee and Chair of the Risk Committee of Save the Children and, in 2001, he and his wife founded Operation Open Arms, a foster care program for children in Louisville, Kentucky. He is a graduate of the University of Colorado and received his MBA with distinction from the Stern School of Business at New York University.